postcontent:
This is a Winchester model 59 “Win-Lite” 12ga semi-auto shotgun.  2 ¾ chamber and modified barrel.

These were made between 1960 and 1965 and designed for light weight.  The receiver is a high-strength aluminum alloy and the barrel is steel lined and wrapped with a synthetic fiber.  The finish is almost identical to a blued barrel and other than the light weight it takes a double take to see that it’s synthetic.  

The receiver is engraved with a Bird dog and pheasant scene on one side and a waterfowl scene on the other.  The Wood stock has checkering on the hand grip and forearm and the trigger guard is gold colored. There is a small nick on the top of the receiver.

This would make a fantastic field shotgun for bird or rabbit hunting

Also included is the original owner’s manual and tag.

title: For Sale:  parker 10mm 1911
postcontent:
The Wyoming Arms Parker is a single action gun somewhat similar to a 1911 Government Model. One major difference, however, is that the Parker has a slide mounted rather than frame mounted manual safety. The Parker can still be carried with the hammer cocked and the safety engaged, but the slide can still be operated so it can't truly be considered "cocked-and-locked" when in this mode. The gun's finish is stainless steel with the flats on the slide brushed while the rest of the gun is bead blasted to a matte gray. The 10mm Parker was available in three barrel lengths including a fixed sighted 3-3/8" gun, a 5" fixed sighted version and a 7" model with adjustable sights.

Double layered, laminated, high strength Mil-spec nylon webbing, triple stitched for rigidity and long life. Cobra Buckle system is unmatched for strength and efficiency. G-Code Active Response / Shooter Belts are an excellent choice for duty, range work or EDC carry as they provide a high quality support solution for your tactical needs. These belts come with available options of; size, color, lining type and with or without D ring. 

Integrated loop is a handy, light weight attachment point for a quick clip item such as keys, lights, gloves or lanyards. NOT to be used as lifting, load bearing attachment point for repelling or extraction.

When buying a belt, it is important to select the correct size based upon an accurate measurement. Your belt size is not the same as your pant or waist size; because your belt goes around you and your pants, tucked in shirt, and your underwear. Your belt size is usually 1 or 2 inches larger than your pant or waist size. G-CODE belts are primarily designed as an outer load bearing belt to carry your holster, magazine carriers, blow-out kit and any other essential items needed. G-CODE belts can also be worn in your belt loops just to hold your pants up. That in mind to get a proper measurement for your belt size using a tape measure, measure around what you will be wearing to determine what size belt you will need in inches. G-CODE Belts are measured by the actual usable length of the belt inside circumference, with a 4 inch adjustment parameter. Example a Large belt inside minimum circumference is 36 inches and can be adjusted out to 40 inches. If your measurement is between 36 and 40 inches you will need a Large.

title: For Sale:   #2023 Smith ( Poultney & Trimble) Civil War carbine, 50-caliber percussion.
postcontent: #2023 Smith ( Poultney & Trimble) Civil War carbine, 50-caliber percussion. Along with the Spencer, Burnside, Maynard, and Sharps, the Smith was one of the "Big Five" main issued Northern carbines during the Civil War and was issued to several Federal and state units. Condition is excellent overall ....almost mint except that the casecolors have faded to a swirly grey for the most part ....and there is a bruise on the forestock from being bounced against some hard object at one time. Other than that it has 99% of the military soft blue finish on the barrel, 80-90% of the glassy blue on the triggerguard and related parts, a mint unfired (I think) bore, and wood that would rate near-mint if not for the one small area of forearm dings. Excellent deeply struck Federal acceptance cartouche on the left wrist. Overall, this is a carbine that will be VERY hard to improve on without getting into the five-thousand-dollar and over price range; definitely investment grade and quality. Excellent. $1995.

title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER SUPREME ELITE 460 S&W Magnum
postcontent:
I have five (5) boxes (20 rounds per box) of this ammo; they are all factory-new and in excellent condition. This is one of the fastest and hardest hitting rounds you can get, and it will effectively drop deer, wild hogs and brown bears. As previously noted, these are factory loaded rounds but, if you choose to do so, they can be reloaded.

These rounds are Winchester’s Dual Bonded Jacketed Hollow Points. According to Winchester, the dual bonding welds the inner jacket to the lead core then takes a heavy outer jacket and mechanically bonds it to the inner bullet which results in deep penetration, exceptional knockdown power and weight retention close to 100%. Upon impact, the outer jacket deploys into 6 equal segments for quick and massive expansion. After penetration, the inner jacket opens into 6 segments to create a total of 12 segments for double the amount of expansion. This gives the hunter a round that delivers a clean, quick kill.

Technical Information 
•  Caliber: 460 S&W Magnum 
•  Bullet Weight: 260 Grains 
•  Bullet Style: Jacketed Hollow Point Dual Bonded 
•  Case Type: Nickel Plated Brass 

Ballistics Information: 
•  Muzzle Velocity: 2000 
•  Muzzle Energy: 2309 ft. lbs.

If you have ever priced these rounds, you know they sell for $58.00 - $69.00 per box. I don’t have a 460; I bought these for my nephew, but then found out he sold his gun and no longer has a need for them either. So, they are just taking up space in my safe that I can use for other ammo. As such, I have these priced to sell.  

Buyer MUST be over 21; provide a phone number and a copy of a valid/current driver’s license; the address on the license must be the same as the ‘ship to’ address. Buyer responsible for compliance with all laws and ordinances and will pay actual UPS shipping charges.
